# Tournament Deploy Safety

Never run `git commit`, `git push`, create a PR, merge, deploy, or trigger any workflow that can redeploy production until you ask:

> Is a tournament live right now?

Only proceed if the user explicitly answers `No`.

If the user says `Yes`, is unsure, or does not answer clearly, do not commit, push, merge, deploy, or trigger Railway. Continue with local edits and validation only.

This applies even when the user asks to "commit", "push", "ship", "deploy", or "quick fix" unless they have already answered that no tournament is live in the current conversation.
